      and the Coming of the Civil War</i>. 
    <p><b>Richard Croker</b> is the author of <i>To Make Men Free, A Novel of 
      the Battle of Antietam</i> (William Morrow/HarperCollins, 2004). The sequel, 
      <i>No Greater Courage, A Novel of the Battle of Fredericksburg</i> is due 
      out in March, 2006 from the same publisher. Croker is an independent documentary 
      filmmaker who lives in Marietta, Georgia.</p>
    <p><b>Cornelius Cronin</b> is a Career Instructor in the English Department 
      at Louisiana State University, where he teaches a course on the literature 
      of modern warfare and writes on literature and film from the Vietnam conflict.</p>
    <p> <B>Ian Crowe</B>, a founding director of the Edmund Burke Society of America, 
