    <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b>Mark Lause</b> is a 
    Professor of History at the University of Cincinnati, who specializes in social 
    history and social movements of the Civil War period. His most recent books 
    covered the emergence of a tri-racial Union Army on the western frontier and 
    the origins of bohemianism in the same years. 
